description: From French retracer, from Middle French retracier.

entries.meaning: (television) The period when the beam of the cathode-ray tube returns to its initial horizontal position in order to start the next line of the display.

verbs.description: retrace (third-person singular simple present retraces, present participle retracing, simple past and past participle retraced)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To trace (a line, etc. in drawing) again.
(transitive) To go back over something, usually in an attempt of rediscovery.
examples: He retraced his steps, and found his keys where he had dropped them.
